cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper presents a meta-learning framework for optimizing different task objectives with respect to different sets of parameters. This is a common problem in machine learning, and the paper applies the framework to four different ML tasks, including image generation and neural machine translation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
